I'm sorry, I missed the reprise.
My fault. Go on.

1037
01:16:04,559 --> 01:16:06,227
All right. Again.

1038
01:16:30,416 --> 01:16:33,919
In their eyes,
I can see the desire to flee,

1039
01:16:34,003 --> 01:16:36,422
to build a hut way up in the sky.

1040
01:16:36,505 --> 01:16:38,882
This fine weather makes them sad.

1041
01:16:57,900 --> 01:17:00,569
You have to see this. It's important.

1042
01:17:03,655 --> 01:17:06,157
While I was cleaning graffiti
off the toilet walls,

1043
01:17:06,241 --> 01:17:08,618
I lifted a stone and found this.

1044
01:17:09,285 --> 01:17:11,495
- That's Corbin's harmonica.
- And that.

1045
01:17:11,579 --> 01:17:13,581
It's 200,000 or more.

1046
01:17:22,881 --> 01:17:25,050
No one knew about your hideaway.

1047
01:17:26,509 --> 01:17:29,470
So don't tell me
it was there by chance.

1048
01:17:29,512 --> 01:17:32,431
You know they expelled Mondain
because of the theft.

1049
01:17:32,515 --> 01:17:34,391
I didn't know.

1050
01:17:34,475 --> 01:17:37,436
That's true. You didn't know.

1051
01:17:37,478 --> 01:17:39,396
Now you know.

1052
01:17:39,438 --> 01:17:41,857
Why? What did you want to do with it?

1053
01:17:43,233 --> 01:17:45,735
If I tell you,
will you tell anyone else?

1054
01:17:45,819 --> 01:17:47,362
No one.

1055
01:17:47,403 --> 01:17:49,322
I swear.

1056
01:17:51,240 --> 01:17:53,242
I wanted to buy...

1057
01:17:53,325 --> 01:17:55,160
To buy what?

1058
01:17:55,953 --> 01:17:57,996
A hot air balloon.

1059
01:17:59,373 --> 01:18:02,292
I don't know who took it,
but it proves Mondain's innocence.

1060
01:18:02,375 --> 01:18:04,711
He'd never have left without the money.

1061
01:18:04,753 --> 01:18:07,130
I'll investigate when I come back.

1062
01:18:07,213 --> 01:18:09,173
But don't worry about it, Mathieu.

1063
01:18:09,257 --> 01:18:13,094
Even if Mondain was innocent,
it won't last. We can't help his type.

1064
01:18:13,177 --> 01:18:16,347
- What about justice?
- Let her take care of him.

1065
01:18:16,388 --> 01:18:18,557
Headmaster, wait for me.
Wait for me.

1066
01:18:18,599 --> 01:18:20,475
Are you leaving too?

1067
01:18:20,517 --> 01:18:23,520
I'm getting a lift. I'm spending
the holidays with relatives.

1068
01:18:23,561 --> 01:18:25,271
At my sister's house.

1069
01:18:26,397 --> 01:18:28,149
They have a piano.

1070
01:18:37,407 --> 01:18:39,243
Do you know why Rachin
went to Lyon?

1071
01:18:39,326 --> 01:18:43,038
I think he's supposed to discuss
the balance sheet with the committee.

1072
01:18:44,164 --> 01:18:45,707
- No?
- Yes.

1073
01:18:45,790 --> 01:18:49,419
But he's mostly going to run
after a promotion and a medal.

1074
01:18:50,545 --> 01:18:52,922
Do you think he'll get them?

1075
01:18:52,963 --> 01:18:56,633
He's really smart. He's going
to present an impeccable report

1076
01:18:56,675 --> 01:18:59,886
without saying a word
about all the horrible things.

1077
01:18:59,970 --> 01:19:02,764
He'll even claim the success
of the chorus for himself.

1078
01:19:02,847 --> 01:19:03,807
Success?

1079
01:19:03,890 --> 01:19:06,351
Certainly. I heard them.
They're good.

1080
01:19:07,310 --> 01:19:10,146
Sir, is it true that
Langlois left with the head?

1081
01:19:10,188 --> 01:19:13,399
Yes. Chabert and Carpentier
have taken two weeks' holidays.

1082
01:19:13,441 --> 01:19:15,901
- We're in charge.
- There's no class today?

1083
01:19:17,986 --> 01:19:19,321
No.

1084
01:19:19,363 --> 01:19:21,782
- What are we going to do?
- Take a nap.

1085
01:19:21,865 --> 01:19:24,242
I have a better idea.

1086
01:19:28,496 --> 01:19:30,039
Thank you.

1087
01:19:30,122 --> 01:19:33,084
I don't want to...

1088
01:19:33,167 --> 01:19:35,461
- Your rosette?
- Yes.

1089
01:19:37,171 --> 01:19:39,548
The bird is in the nest, Mr. Rachin.

1090
01:19:41,049 --> 01:19:43,260
I can't thank you enough.

1091
01:19:45,470 --> 01:19:48,264
I'm sorry, Headmaster.
You're wanted on the telephone.

1092
01:19:53,936 --> 01:19:55,437
I'm sorry.

1093
01:20:12,703 --> 01:20:14,038
Headmaster!

1094
01:20:14,997 --> 01:20:17,666
- Do something. My son is up there.
- Let me through.

1095
01:20:18,000 --> 01:20:20,127
The fire had caught under the eaves.

1096
01:20:20,210 --> 01:20:23,922
The dormitories, where the children
had last been seen, were in flames.

1097
01:20:24,005 --> 01:20:26,007
Sixty unfortunate children,

1098
01:20:26,090 --> 01:20:28,176
caught in a snare.

1099
01:20:28,259 --> 01:20:30,803
Rachin saw his promotion
and his rosette

1100
01:20:30,845 --> 01:20:32,930
destroyed before his very eyes.

1101
01:20:33,013 --> 01:20:34,723
But, suddenly...

1102
01:21:22,058 --> 01:21:26,187
After breakfast, we used the door
leading out of the vegetable patch

1103
01:21:26,229 --> 01:21:29,232
to avoid old Marie and the villagers.

1104
01:21:29,315 --> 01:21:31,150
We went to the forest of Lignan.

1105
01:21:31,192 --> 01:21:33,402
For what purpose?

1106
01:21:33,486 --> 01:21:36,822
A treasure hunt.
They were so happy.

1107
01:21:39,950 --> 01:21:43,953
I don't need to tell you
how disappointed I am, Mr. Maxence.

1108
01:21:44,037 --> 01:21:46,831
This was entirely my idea, Headmaster.

1109
01:21:46,915 --> 01:21:50,501
Mr. Maxence never stopped
trying to dissuade me.

1110
01:21:50,585 --> 01:21:52,128
Not very convincing.

1111
01:21:52,169 --> 01:21:55,965
We could also consider the fact
that we saved the children's lives.

1112
01:21:56,048 --> 01:21:59,509
If you hadn't left the school,
it wouldn't have caught fire.

1113
01:21:59,593 --> 01:22:02,012
I don't even know
why I'm listening to you.

1114
01:22:02,095 --> 01:22:06,933
Mr. Maxence, owing to your long years
of service, I'll just suspend you.

1115
01:22:07,976 --> 01:22:10,478
As for you, Mr. Mathieu, you're fired.

1116
01:22:10,561 --> 01:22:12,646
For breaking the rules.

1117
01:22:12,688 --> 01:22:14,607
Then you should fire me too.

1118
01:22:14,648 --> 01:22:16,525
You don't get to decide.

1119
01:22:16,608 --> 01:22:20,529
It's nice of you, Mr. Maxence,
but you're needed here.

1120
01:22:20,612 --> 01:22:23,907
Think about the children,
since this gentleman never does.

1121
01:22:27,035 --> 01:22:29,287
I've settled up with you. Here.

1122
01:22:29,328 --> 01:22:32,456
You're leaving right now,
on the 6:00 bus.

1123
01:22:32,498 --> 01:22:35,542
You're allowed no contact
with your former students. None.

1124
01:22:35,626 --> 01:22:38,003
- What?
- Mr. Maxence, see to it.

1125
01:22:38,086 --> 01:22:39,796
Get out.

1126
01:22:43,800 --> 01:22:49,013
Headmaster, before I go,
I'll tell you what I think of you.

1127
01:22:49,097 --> 01:22:52,058
- I already know, Mathieu.
- You're an incompetent,

1128
01:22:52,099 --> 01:22:54,143
- truly evil man.
- What about them?

1129
01:22:54,226 --> 01:22:56,103
They're not here by choice.

1130
01:22:56,186 --> 01:22:58,438
Neither am I.
I never wanted to be a teacher.

1131
01:22:58,480 --> 01:23:01,358
Don't tell me you wanted to come
to that miserable place.

1132
01:23:01,441 --> 01:23:04,444
- You had other ambitions? So did I.
- Don't take it out on them.

1133
01:23:04,486 --> 01:23:06,905
Do you think I like being a warden?

1134
01:23:06,946 --> 01:23:08,823
Someone has to do it.

1135
01:23:08,906 --> 01:23:12,034
Pack up your bags and go to Paris.
Make the Ministry rounds.

1136
01:23:12,118 --> 01:23:14,078
Knock-knock.
"Hello. My name is Mathieu.

1137
01:23:14,161 --> 01:23:16,288
We need real teachers
instead of washouts."

1138
01:23:16,372 --> 01:23:18,749
Fight for the cause
if you believe in it, Mathieu.

1139
01:23:18,832 --> 01:23:21,042
Saint Mathieu.

1140
01:23:21,126 --> 01:23:23,295
You're nothing but a failed musician.

1141
01:23:23,378 --> 01:23:26,339
A prefect. A small prefect.
Small, small, small.

1142
01:23:26,965 --> 01:23:29,634
"What do you do, Mr. Mathieu?"
"I'm a prefect."

1143
01:23:29,675 --> 01:23:32,053
Small. Small. Small.

1144
01:23:33,137 --> 01:23:34,555
You're crazy.

1145
01:23:34,638 --> 01:23:36,140
I'm tired.

1146
01:23:36,223 --> 01:23:37,808
Go to the devil.

1147
01:23:37,891 --> 01:23:40,268
No, I'm leaving him behind.

1148
01:23:52,780 --> 01:23:57,076
I had hoped a few students
would break the rules to say goodbye.

1149
01:23:57,117 --> 01:23:59,036
I saw no one.

1150
01:23:59,119 --> 01:24:02,289
The wisdom of these children
came across as indifference.

1151
01:24:02,914 --> 01:24:05,250
And Morhange...

1152
01:24:05,291 --> 01:24:07,043
Enough.

1153
01:24:25,101 --> 01:24:26,895
"See you soon, Mr. Mathieu."

1154
01:24:26,978 --> 01:24:28,396
"Goodbye, Chrome Dome."

1155
01:24:37,196 --> 01:24:40,365
On the first note, I recognized
Boniface's careful script.

1156
01:24:40,449 --> 01:24:44,452
The spelling mistakes
were Ppinot's, of course.

1157
01:24:44,536 --> 01:24:47,955
This one, filled with music notes,
came from Morhange.

1158
01:24:48,998 --> 01:24:51,083
And this one...

1159
01:24:51,167 --> 01:24:52,585
And that one...

1160
01:25:16,315 --> 01:25:18,192
Be silent! Make them stop!

1161
01:25:18,233 --> 01:25:20,360
The door's locked.

1162
01:25:20,444 --> 01:25:22,028
Open up!

1163
01:25:22,779 --> 01:25:26,074
Right then I felt a sudden burst
ofjoy and optimism.

1164
01:25:26,157 --> 01:25:28,534
I wanted to share it
with the entire world.

1165
01:25:28,618 --> 01:25:30,536
But who would have listened?

1166
01:25:30,620 --> 01:25:33,289
No one even knew I was alive.

1167
01:25:34,165 --> 01:25:37,084
The great artist would soon
give way to the ordinary man.

1168
01:25:38,043 --> 01:25:40,087
I'm Clment Mathieu,

1169
01:25:40,170 --> 01:25:42,964
a failed musician,
an unemployed prefect.

1170
01:25:43,048 --> 01:25:45,049
"I'm Clment Mathieu,

1171
01:25:45,133 --> 01:25:48,803
a failed musician,
an unemployed prefect."

1172
01:26:02,232 --> 01:26:04,401
What happened next?

1173
01:26:04,442 --> 01:26:07,320
He never finished his journal.

1174
01:26:09,780 --> 01:26:12,408
But I can tell you the story.

1175
01:26:14,451 --> 01:26:17,204
Ppinot answered my questions.

1176
01:26:17,246 --> 01:26:22,083
The following day, on the way back,
my childhood caught me by the throat.

1177
01:26:23,251 --> 01:26:26,880
When Mathieu was fired,
my mother took me back home.

1178
01:26:26,963 --> 01:26:29,966
We left for Lyon, where
I was admitted to the Conservatory.

1179
01:26:31,467 --> 01:26:33,844
The engineer tried
to send me to boarding school.

1180
01:26:33,928 --> 01:26:36,680
She refused. He left us.

1181
01:26:37,389 --> 01:26:43,144
Chabert, Langlois and old Maxence
joined forces to expose Rachin's abuse.

1182
01:26:43,186 --> 01:26:47,106
The children were questioned
and Rachin was fired.

1183
01:26:51,944 --> 01:26:55,614
Clment Mathieu gave music lessons
for the rest of his life,

1184
01:26:55,698 --> 01:26:58,075
without courting notoriety.

1185
01:26:58,158 --> 01:27:00,744
Everything he did, he kept for himself.

1186
01:27:01,995 --> 01:27:04,873
For himself? No, not quite.

1187
01:27:04,914 --> 01:27:06,666
Mr. Mathieu.

1188
01:27:09,001 --> 01:27:10,711
Mr. Mathieu.

1189
01:27:13,005 --> 01:27:14,673
Wait a bit.

1190
01:27:17,509 --> 01:27:19,428
Mr. Mathieu.

1191
01:27:24,974 --> 01:27:26,142
What are you doing?

1192
01:27:26,226 --> 01:27:28,728
Can you take me with you?

1193
01:27:28,811 --> 01:27:30,188
Sir.

1194
01:27:30,229 --> 01:27:34,024
I can't do that. You have to go back
to school. They'll punish you.

1195
01:27:34,108 --> 01:27:35,067
Please?

1196
01:27:35,150 --> 01:27:37,277
- Can we go now?
- Coming.

1197
01:27:37,361 --> 01:27:40,405
It's forbidden.
I can't take you with me.

1198
01:27:40,489 --> 01:27:42,073
Go back.

1199
01:27:42,157 --> 01:27:43,742
Go on.

1200
01:27:44,075 --> 01:27:45,660
Go on.

1201
01:28:10,183 --> 01:28:12,685
Ppinot had been right all along.

1202
01:28:12,768 --> 01:28:15,437
Mathieu was fired on a Saturday.